From: ezLegal.ai prototype
Subject: [PATCH] Home hero, primary nav, and KPI strip alignment with prototype

Scope: Bring dev.ezlegal.ai home page and top navigation in line with the
current Bolt prototype. Three logical changes bundled:

  1. Home hero - copy, CrisisStrip, TrustChip (replaces static pills),
     "Ask a free legal question" primary CTA wired to /start with
     consent recording, and "Privacy at a glance" legal line.
  2. HomeKPIStrip - 4-up stat strip below hero, live counts from Supabase
     (chat_messages count, lawyer_profiles partner count).
  3. Top Navigation - header CTA renamed "Ask free" -> "Ask a question",
     top-level groups consolidated to Get Help / Why ezLegal / Pricing
     via consolidateNavGroups().

New/changed runtime dependencies: none. All components already exist in
src/components/. The patch only wires them together in Home.tsx and
updates one copy string in Navigation.tsx.

Supabase: no schema changes required for this PR. HomeKPIStrip reads
existing tables (chat_messages, lawyer_profiles) via the anon client and
degrades gracefully when counts are null.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
 src/pages/Home.tsx          | hero section (lines 82-174)
 src/components/Navigation.tsx | header CTA label + top-group filter
---------------------------------------------------------------------

